# AWS Hybrid Cloud Connectivity with Terraform

## Overview

This repository demonstrates a modular AWS infrastructure deployment using Terraform, GitHub Actions, and OIDC authentication. The project is designed to showcase enterprise-grade Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) practices commonly used in hybrid cloud and fintech environments.

The architecture focuses on scalable cloud networking, reusable Terraform modules, CI/CD automation, and secure GitHub-to-AWS authentication.

---

## Key Features

- Modular Terraform architecture
- Reusable VPC and EC2 modules
- GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines
- OIDC authentication between GitHub and AWS
- Remote Terraform state management
- Infrastructure automation best practices
- AWS networking deployment patterns

---

